---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is ZE a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL (11 Points)"
  description="ZE is valid in SOWPODS (Collins) but NOT in TWL. Worth 11 points in international play, ZE is a gender-neutral pronoun. Check your dictionary before playing this word."
  keywords="is ze a scrabble word, ze scrabble valid, ze sowpods, ze twl invalid, gender neutral pronoun scrabble, z words scrabble, two letter z words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is ZE a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL",
    "description": "ZE is valid in SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words) but NOT valid in TWL (Tournament Word List). Worth 11 points in international play, it's a gender-neutral pronoun.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-23",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-ze-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is ZE a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "ZE is valid ONLY in SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words), used in international, UK, and Australian tournaments. It is NOT valid in TWL (Tournament Word List), used in North American NASPA-sanctioned play." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What does ZE mean?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "ZE is a gender-neutral pronoun used as an alternative to 'he' or 'she.' It was added to Collins Scrabble Words in 2014 to reflect evolving English usage." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Should I play ZE or ZA?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "If you're unsure which dictionary your game uses, always play ZA instead. ZA is valid in BOTH TWL and SOWPODS, scores the same 11 points, and carries zero risk of challenge. Only play ZE if you're certain the game uses Collins/SOWPODS." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Validity</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is ZE a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">ZE is one of those tricky Scrabble words that depends entirely on which dictionary you're playing with. Valid in SOWPODS (Collins) for international play but rejected in TWL for North American tournaments, ZE can either score you 11 easy points or cost you a turn. Here's everything you need to know before risking this controversial 2-letter Z play.</p>

      <!-- Hero Card (warning style) -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-red-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">⚠️ Dictionary-Dependent</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">ZE</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">11 points · Z(10) + E(1) · Gender-neutral pronoun · SOWPODS only</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">ZE is valid in Collins Scrabble Words (international) but INVALID in TWL (North America). It's a gender-neutral pronoun meaning "he or she." Playing this in the wrong dictionary costs you your turn.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points (SOWPODS)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-red-400">✗</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Invalid in TWL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">✓</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid in Collins</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2014</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Added to Collins</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Dictionary Comparison</h2>
      <p>ZE's validity splits along dictionary lines — know your game before you play:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ INVALID in TWL (NASPA)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Not in Tournament Word List. Playing ZE in North American NASPA tournaments results in a challenge loss and tile recall.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Valid in SOWPODS (Collins)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Accepted in Collins since 2014. Legal in all international tournaments, UK/Australian clubs, and Collins-based online games.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What Does ZE Mean?</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">📖 Definition</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">ZE is a <span class="text-white font-medium">gender-neutral pronoun</span> used as a substitute for "he" or "she." Part of the ze/hir pronoun set adopted by some non-binary individuals. Collins added it to reflect evolving English usage. Example: "Ze walked to the park."</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">When to Risk Playing ZE</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">International tournaments:</span> If playing SOWPODS/Collins, ZE is 100% safe. Play it freely on premium squares.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Online games:</span> Check game settings for "Collins" or "SOWPODS." If confirmed, ZE is safe. If "TWL" or "NASPA" — don't risk it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">When in doubt — play ZA:</span> ZA scores the same 11 points and is valid in BOTH dictionaries. Zero risk, same reward.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Safe Z Alternatives (Both Dictionaries)</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZAP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZEN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZED</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZIT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZERO</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts ✓</span></span>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-za-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is ZA a Scrabble Word? 11 Points (Both Dictionaries)</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-z-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Z Words for Scrabble: Complete High-Scoring Guide</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-ew-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is EW a Scrabble Word? Another SOWPODS-Only Controversy</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word's validity in both TWL and SOWPODS — free, instant, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
